I now have a complete picture of the implementation. Here is the full findings report.

---

## Research Findings: AI Daily Report "Thinking" Effect

All relevant code lives in two files:

### 1. AiChatPanel.vue — The AI Chat Interface

**File:** `D:/project/info-gitlab/oa/oa-frontend/src/app/PC/StaffPage/OaDailyReport/OthersReports/AiChatPanel.vue`

---

#### Template — Three-stage rendering (lines 95–105)

The bubble area uses three mutually exclusive states driven by `isStreaming` (a boolean data property) and whether `m.content` is empty:

```html
<!-- Outer bubble: shown when content exists OR streaming the last assistant message -->
<div v-else-if="m.content || (isStreaming && i === messages.length - 1 && m.role === 'assistant')" class="bubble">

    <!-- Stage 1: THINKING — shown while streaming but no content has arrived yet -->
    <span v-if="isStreaming && i === messages.length - 1 && m.role === 'assistant' && !m.content" class="ai-thinking">
        <span class="ai-thinking-dot"></span>
        <span class="ai-thinking-dot"></span>
        <span class="ai-thinking-dot"></span>
    </span>

    <!-- Stage 2/3: CONTENT + optional typing cursor -->
    <template v-else>
        <span v-if="m.role === 'assistant'" v-html="renderMd(m.content)"></span>
        <span v-else>{{ m.content }}</span>
        <!-- Blinking cursor shown while stream is still live -->
        <span v-if="isStreaming && i === messages.length - 1 && m.role === 'assistant'" class="typing-cursor"></span>
    </template>
</div>
```

So the three distinct visual states are:

| State | Condition | Visual |
|---|---|---|
| Thinking dots | `isStreaming && !m.content` | Three bouncing dots |
| Streaming text | `isStreaming && m.content` | Markdown text + blinking cursor |
| Done | `!isStreaming` | Markdown text, no cursor |

---

#### Data property (line 278)

```ts
isStreaming = false
private streamAbort: AbortController | null = null
```

`isStreaming` is set to `true` right before the SSE stream starts (line 742/553), and reset to `false` in the `finally` block once the stream ends or is aborted.

---

#### CSS/Animation (lines 1260–1292)

```less
// AI 思考中（三点跳动）
.ai-thinking {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    padding: 2px 0;
}
.ai-thinking-dot {
    width: 7px;
    height: 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #909399;
    animation: thinking-bounce 1.2s ease-in-out infinite;
    &:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0s; }
    &:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }
    &:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }
}
@keyframes thinking-bounce {
    0%, 80%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); opacity: 0.4; }
    40%           { transform: translateY(-5px); opacity: 1; }
}

// 打字光标
.typing-cursor {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 2px;
    height: 13px;
    background: currentColor;
    margin-left: 2px;
    vertical-align: text-bottom;
    animation: blink .7s step-end infinite;
}
@keyframes blink { 50% { opacity: 0; } }
```

Three grey 7px circles, staggered 0.2s apart, each bouncing up 5px and fading from 0.4 to 1 opacity over 1.2s. The typing cursor is a 2x13px vertical bar blinking at 0.7s intervals using `step-end` (instant toggle, not fade).

There is also a skeleton shimmer (`@keyframes shimmer`) used for the role list loading state (not the AI thinking state).

---

### 2. PromptTestDialog.vue — The "Test Prompt" Dialog

**File:** `D:/project/info-gitlab/oa/oa-frontend/src/app/PC/StaffPage/OaDailyReport/OthersReports/PromptTestDialog.vue`

This is a separate, simpler dialog used by admins to test AI prompt configurations. It does NOT use the three-dot animation. Instead it uses a step-machine:

```ts
step: 'loading' | 'streaming' | 'done' | 'error' = 'loading'
```

- **`loading`**: Shows `<i class="el-icon-loading" />` (Element UI's CSS spinner) + the text `正在查询日报数据并分析...`
- **`streaming`**: Shows the streamed Markdown content (rendered via `markdown-it`) + a "停止" button
- **`done`**: Same as streaming view but "停止" button disappears
- **`error`**: Shows `<i class="el-icon-warning" />` + error message

The loading spinner is entirely delegated to Element UI's built-in `el-icon-loading` class — no custom keyframe animation in this component.

The dialog calls `dailyReportAiApis.testEmailTask(...)` using the Fetch API + `ReadableStream` / `TextDecoder` for SSE parsing, with an `AbortController` for the stop button.

---

### Summary of all animations found

| Animation | File | Class | Keyframe | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Three bouncing dots | AiChatPanel.vue | `.ai-thinking-dot` | `thinking-bounce` (1.2s, staggered) | "Waiting for first token" state |
| Blinking cursor | AiChatPanel.vue | `.typing-cursor` | `blink` (0.7s step-end) | "Token streaming in progress" state |
| Spin | AiChatPanel.vue | (roles loading) | `spin` (1s linear) | Role list loading spinner |
| Shimmer | AiChatPanel.vue | `.sk-avatar`, `.sk-line` | `shimmer` (1.2s) | Skeleton loading for role list |
| el-icon-loading | PromptTestDialog.vue | (Element UI built-in) | (external) | Initial data fetch in test dialog |
